#### Geolocate Eventbrite events

## Search events from eventbrite and place the event on the map

## Pre-requisites
OS: *nix

Dependencies
* Java 6
* Flex 4 SDK
* ArcGIS Flex API 2.5
* Ant 1.8.3
* Eventbrite API Key

## Installation instruction 

# Set environment variables
export JAVA_HOME={root of the java installation - e.g. /usr
export ANT_HOME={Directory where you installed Ant}
export FLEX_HOME={Directory where you install Flex}
export PATH=${PATH}:${ANT_HOME}/bin

# Set configuration file.
* Open config/Config.xml
* Set each configuration parmaeter with appropriate value
* Put your Eventbrite API Key into config/AppKey.txt.
  API Key should be on the first line of config/AppKey.txt,
  and it should be the only thing on that line.

# Go to the root of the checkout directory and build app
% cd {root of the checkout}
% ant -lib ${FLEX_HOME}/ant/lib/flexTasks.jar main

